                                    <layout columns="1" writtenLines="41 47">
                                        <locus from="88r" to="135r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <note>Guidelines in ink.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">Gothic cursive (the scribe is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102763">Jan Hus</persName>).</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>The page is ruled in ink for two columns. The entire left column and 5 lines of the right column are filled with a theological text in a rapid cursive hand. Bottom right corner, in ink: <quote>13.</quote>, <quote>9.</quote>. This leaf is attached to the first quire, but did probably originally not belong to it.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in ink in a modern hand: <quote>Johannis wycleph Th. D. tractatus duo. 1<hi rend="super">us</hi> de individuacione temporis. 2<hi rend="super">us</hi> de veris <del>-tatibus</del>
                                            <add place="below">universalibus</add>. </quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="3v" to="134r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal and interlinear additions by one or several contemporary hands (perhaps the scribe). Some leaves, e.g. <locus from="7r" to="7r" scheme="folios"/>, contain copious additions. The additions seem to consist mainly of corrections and additions of omitted text.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locusGrp>
                                        <locus from="35r" to="35r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="75v" to="75v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="87v" to="87v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="112r" to="112r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="147v" to="147v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    </locusGrp>
                                    <note>National Library stamp.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="147Ar" to="147Av" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>This loose leaf seems to be written by the same hand and with the same type of content as the text on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink; rubrics in red; capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="132r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 2-3 lines in red. The opening initial C on <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/> and the initial Q on <locus from="26v" to="26v" scheme="folios"/> embellished with flourishing and an acanthus leaf in brown and red ink in the counterspace.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
